Class FunctionDefinitionSet<O,I>

    I - the java class for the data type of the function Input arguments

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    FunctionDefinition

    public class FunctionDefinitionSet<O,I>
extends FunctionDefinitionBase<O,I>
    FunctionDefinitionSet implements FunctionDefinition to implement the XACML Set predicates as functions taking two arguments of Bag the same primitive type and returning either a Boolean or a Bag of the same primitive type.

    The ipAddress, dnsName and xPathExpression do not have set functions defined for them in section 10.2.8 of the Release 3 XACML spec. In the first implementation of XACML we had separate files for each XACML Function. This release combines multiple Functions in fewer files to minimize code duplication. This file supports the following XACML codes: string-bag boolean-bag integer-bag double-bag time-bag date-bag dateTime-bag anyURI-bag hexBinary-bag base64Binary-bag dayTimeDuration-bag (version 1 and3) yearMonthDuration-bag (version 1 and 3) x500Name-bag rfc822Name-bag

    Version:
    $Revision: 1.1 $
